Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 17:13:06 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Docs link to all remaining sidebar copies
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The 'Docs' nav item was only added to app/dashboard/page.tsx's
sidebar. Since this sidebar is duplicated (not shared) across the
app — same pattern we hit when enabling Brownfield — it was missing
from the other 5 pages: Brownfield input page, Brownfield detail
page, Knowledge Base page, Settings page, and Blueprint detail page.

Added the same Docs -> /doc link, in the same position (right after
Settings), to:
- components/brownfield/BrownfieldClient.tsx
- components/brownfield/BrownfieldDetailClient.tsx
- components/knowledge-base/KnowledgeBaseClient.tsx
- components/settings/SettingsClient.tsx
- components/blueprint/BlueprintDetailClient.tsx

Note: app/project/new/page.tsx (Greenfield wizard) has no
Configuration section in its sidebar at all — that's a pre-existing
gap unrelated to Docs, not touched here.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, next build succeeds (23/23 pages),
diff confirmed as exactly 5 files / 15 lines, additions only.
---
 components/blueprint/BlueprintDetailClient.tsx    | 3 +++
 components/brownfield/BrownfieldClient.tsx        | 3 +++
 components/brownfield/BrownfieldDetailClient.tsx  | 3 +++
 components/knowledge-base/KnowledgeBaseClient.tsx | 3 +++
 components/settings/SettingsClient.tsx            | 3 +++
 5 files changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/components/blueprint/BlueprintDetailClient.tsx b/components/blueprint/BlueprintDetailClient.tsx
index 2dab4ce..82211c2 100644
--- a/components/blueprint/BlueprintDetailClient.tsx
+++ b/components/blueprint/BlueprintDetailClient.tsx
@@ -154,6 +154,9 @@ export default function BlueprintDetailClient({ blueprint, user }: Props) {
